.TH OPENTELEMETRY-INJECTOR 8 "@DATE@" "opentelemetry-injector @VERSION@" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
opentelemetry-injector \- LD_PRELOAD-based automatic instrumentation injector
.SH DESCRIPTION
The OpenTelemetry Injector is a shared library that, when loaded via
.BR ld.so.preload (5),
automatically instruments applications running on the system.
.PP
It detects the runtime environment (Java, Node.js, .NET) of each process
and injects the appropriate OpenTelemetry auto-instrumentation agent.
.SH CONFIGURATION
.TP
.I /etc/opentelemetry/injector/otelinject.conf
Main configuration file for the injector.
.TP
.I /etc/opentelemetry/injector/conf.d/
Drop-in directory for agent path configurations. Each language agent package
installs a fragment here.
.TP
.I /etc/opentelemetry/injector/default_env.conf
Default environment variables applied to all instrumented processes.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/lib/opentelemetry/injector/libotelinject.so
The injector shared library.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ld.so.preload (5)
.PP
https://opentelemetry.io/docs/
